      "Tips": [
        {
          "Text": "Brew Frost Resistance Mead before entering the Mountains — each potion lasts 10 minutes",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Craft a Wolf Fur Cape or Lox Cape as your first Silver item — it permanently removes the freezing debuff",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Equip the Wishbone from Bonemass in high-altitude areas — it pings and sparks when you are above a Silver Vein",
          "Category": "gathering",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Onion Seeds are found in chests inside ruined stone cabins — grow them for Onion Soup, a cheap stamina food",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Look for jagged ice formations on cliff faces — these are Frost Cave entrances containing Fenris Hair and Claws",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Dig a trench completely around a Silver Vein, then hit the center — the whole vein shatters at once",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Dragon Eggs weigh 200kg each and cannot be teleported — haul all 3 to Moder's altar before you start the fight",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Wolf Fur Cape or Lox Cape negates the freezing debuff permanently — craft one before exploring the peaks",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Dig a trench near Moder's altar before summoning — her ice projectiles cannot angle downward into it",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Wolves can be tamed with raw meat — bred wolves produce wolf cubs and eventually Wolf Pelt without hunting",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Stone Golems are immune to all damage types except blunt and pickaxe — a Bronze Pickaxe works fine",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Silver physics pop: dig completely under a Silver vein until it floats, hit the centre — it collapses into loose ore instantly",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },

        {
          "Text": "Haul Dragon Eggs to the Moder altar one at a time — they weigh 200kg each and cannot be teleported",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Dig a trench near the Moder altar — her ice-breath projectiles cannot shoot downward effectively",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Bring your max-upgraded Iron Mace into the Mountains — it is the only weapon that deals good damage to Stone Golems",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Use the Huntsman Bow to shoot Drakes out of the sky before they start harassing you",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Parrying a charging Wolf with your Iron Buckler is safer than blocking — it staggers them for a free counter",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Frostner requires Silver, Ymir Flesh (from Haldor), and Freeze Glands — it slows enemies and is arguably the best all-around weapon",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Draugr Fang bow applies innate poison to every shot — pair it with Obsidian Arrows for massive damage",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        }
      ]
